---
title: Tunisian-Spiced Chicken with Apricot Sauce, Green Beans & Golden Rice Pilaf
description: Sure, you could have plain chicken for dinner—but why would you, when you can dig into this warmly spiced version, smothered in tangy apricot pan sauce? Here, cutlets are seasoned and seared in our Tunisian spice blend of caraway, smoked paprika, turmeric, cayenne, and cinnamon. Green beans are sautéed with the fond (aka the brown bits left by the seared chicken) until crisped and packed with flavor. Meanwhile, jasmine rice steams with the same cozy spices to create a literal pot of gold. All this in 20 minutes? Lucky you!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/tunisian-spiced-chicken-6c001139.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/tunisian-spiced-chicken-624326eb1cad6d76fc606b5b-329cc198.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 24 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 480 mg
cuisine: African
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tunisian-spiced-chicken-624326eb1cad6d76fc606b5b
time required: 20 minutes
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{½%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ¾ cup water, @Tunisian Spice Blend{¼%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use two of the stock concentrates, 1 1/2 cups water, and ½ tsp Tunisian Spice.

Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; place in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{} (use a large bowl for 4 servings) with a splash of water. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}, then drain.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @apricot jam{1}, remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @Tunisian Spice Blend{1%tsp}, @white wine vinegar{1%tsp}, and ½ tsp water. Microwave for ~{45%seconds}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 tsp Tunisian Spice, 2 tsp vinegar, and 1 tsp water.

Stir in @butter{1%TBSP} until melted. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover bowl with plastic wrap to keep warm.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken is taking longer to cook through, reduce heat to medium and cover pan for the last few minutes of cooking.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

While chicken rests, remove green beans from bowl; pat dry with paper towels.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add green beans; cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until green beans are browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @sliced almonds{½%ounce}, @golden raisins{1%ounce}, and @butter{1%TBSP}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Reheat sauce in microwave for ~{10-15%seconds} if necessary.

Divide rice, green beans, and chicken between #plates{}. Drizzle chicken with as much sauce as you like; serve any remaining on the side.